/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  pitzer01_nacl --- the first electrolyte case.

  gamma_pm, the osmotic coefficient phi and the water activity a_w for NaCl,
  by the Pitzer ion-interaction model.  The parameters are CURATED data, read
  by name from data/standards/electrolyte/NaCl.dat (cited: Pitzer & Mayorga
  1973).  Open pitzer_nacl.csv: gamma_pm dips to ~0.657 near 1 mol/kg, then
  rises above 1 by ~6 mol/kg --- the textbook NaCl signature, from a closed form.

  NOTE on the two L_phi columns: pitzer_nacl.csv reports L_phi_fit and
  L_phi_anchored, and they are IDENTICAL in every row.  That is illustrative,
  not a coincidence: the relative apparent molar enthalpy L_phi here is
  derived from the same anchored tau(T) and is calorimetrically UNCALIBRATED
  (no separate fit to heat-of-dilution data yet), so the "fit" column simply
  reproduces the "anchored" one.  Calibrating L_phi against Parker, NSRDS-NBS 2
  (1965) is the intended next step; until then treat the two columns as one.
  The gamma_pm / phi / a_w values are physically sound and need no caveat.
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
operations
(
    {
        name      gamma_nacl;
        type      pitzerActivity;
        cation    Na;
        anion     Cl;
        molality  { from 0.1; to 6.0; n 30; }
        output    { file pitzer_nacl.csv; }
    }
);
